  "name": "Dinosaur Tree",
  "description": "A journey through the age of dinosaurs — from the first tiny hunters of the Triassic to the mighty giants of the Cretaceous. Thirty species organized by the three great periods of the Mesozoic Era, with tiered content for young children (Story) and older readers (Science).\n\nPUBLIC DOMAIN ILLUSTRATION REFERENCES: Charles R. Knight (1874–1953), whose paintings for the American Museum of Natural History defined how generations imagined dinosaurs. Heinrich Harder (1858–1935), German artist known for his prehistoric animal paintings. Zdeněk Burian (1905–1981), Czech paleoartist whose reconstructions shaped European understanding of prehistory.",
